DocuMind AI — Tech Stack Document
1. Architectural Layers
L1 — AI / LLM Core: RAG, embeddings, inference
L2 — Backend API: query handling, orchestration
L3 — Frontend: Chrome Extension + Web App
L4 — Data & Storage: documents, vectors, metadata
L5 — DevOps / Infra: deployment, monitoring, caching
2. Master Tech Stack
L1 — AI / LLM Core
Python 3.11+, Ollama (Mistral 7B, LLaMA 3, Gemma 2), Gemini 1.5 Flash, Groq, LangChain, Sentence Transformers
L2 — Backend API
FastAPI, Uvicorn, Pydantic, Celery + Redis (optional)
L3 — Frontend
React + TypeScript (Chrome Extension, MV3), Next.js 14, Tailwind CSS, Axios
L4 — Data & Storage
ChromaDB (dev), Qdrant (prod), Supabase PostgreSQL, Supabase Auth / NextAuth, Supabase Storage, Cloudflare R2
L5 — Document Processing
PyMuPDF, python-docx, python-pptx, Tesseract OCR
L6 — DevOps & Infra
Vercel, Railway/Render, Redis/Upstash, Grafana, Prometheus, Langfuse, GitHub
3. Tier Classification
Core — Required for MVP
Recommended — Improves performance/scalability
Advanced — Production/enterprise features
4. Key Design Choices
RAG architecture for document Q&A
Local LLM via Ollama for cost efficiency
Qdrant for scalable vector search
FastAPI for high-performance backend
Next.js + React for unified frontend